data.text:
These people of the present and past were born on this date:

Actress Joanne Woodward is 83.

Hall of Fame wide receiver and former NFL coach Raymond Berry is 80.

Political activist and former presidential candidate Ralph Nader is 79.

Opera singer Mirella Freni is 78.

Cardinal Roger Mahony is 77.

Actress Barbara Babcock is 76.

Actor Howard Hesseman (“WKRP in Cincinnati,” “Head of the Class”) is 73.

PBS and NPR journalist Charlayne Hunter-Gault is 71.

Actress Debra Monk (“Grey’s Anatomy,” “The Producers”) is 64.

Guitarist Neal Schon of Journey is 59.

Guitarist Adrian Smith of Iron Maiden is 56.

Actor Timothy Spall (“Harry Potter” movies, “The King’s Speech”) is 56.

Actress Tracey Ross (“Passions”) is 54.

Keyboardist Paul Humphreys of OMD is 53.

Singer Johnny Van Zant of Lynyrd Skynyrd is 53.

Comedian Wendy Liebman is 52.

Actor Grant Shaud (“Murphy Brown,” “Oliver Beene”) is 52.

Basketball Hall of Famer James Worthy is 52.

Actor Adam Baldwin (“Chuck,” “Full Metal Jacket”) is 51.

Actor Grant Show (“Melrose Place”) is 51.

Baseball announcer Chip Caray is 47.

Guitarist Mike Cross of Sponge is 48.

Actor Noah Emmerich (“The Americans,” “Super 8”) is 48.

Actor Donal Logue (“Knights of Prosperity,” “Grounded for Life”) is 47.

Hall of Fame jockey Kent Desormeaux is 43.

Singer Rozonda “Chilli” Thomas (TLC) is 42.

Keyboardist Jeremy Dean of Nine Days is 41.

Singer Roderick Clark (Hi-Five) is 40.

Actress Li Bingbing (“Resident Evil: Retribution,” “The Forbidden Kingdom”) is 40.

Former NFL running back Duce Staley is 38.

Atlanta Falcons tight end Tony Gonzalez, a graduate of Huntington Beach High School, is 37.

Director and producer James Wan (“Saw” films, “House of Horror”) is 36.

Bassist Shonna Tucker of Drive-By Truckers is 35.

Actor Brandon Beemer (“The Bold and the Beautiful,” “Days of Our Lives”) is 33.

TV journalist and former first daughter Chelsea Clinton is 33.

Singer Bobby Valentino is 33.

Singer Josh Groban is 32.

Drummer Jared Champion of Cage the Elephant is 30.

Actress Hayley Holt (“Flick”) is 30.

Actress Kate Mara (“American Horror Story,” “127 Hours”) is 30.

Model Nicole Linkletter (“America’s Next Top Model”) is 28.

Milwaukee Brewers pitcher Yovani Gallardo is 27.

Singer Stefano Langone (“American Idol”) is 24.

Birthdays of the past:

1807 Henry Wadsworth Longfellow, poet; died 1882.

1886 Hugo Black, U.S. senator and longtime Supreme Court justice; died 1971.

1891 David Sarnoff, TV pioneer; died 1971.

1897 Marian Anderson, singer; died 1993.

1902 Gene Sarazen, Hall of Fame golfer; died 1999.

1902 John Steinbeck, author; died 1968.

1907 Mildred Bailey, singer; died 1951

1910 Joan Bennett, actress; died 1990.

1917 John Connally, Texas governor, U.S. Secretary of the Treasury and Secretary of the Navy; died 1993

1923 Dexter Gordon, jazz saxophonist; died 1990.

1932 Elizabeth Taylor, actress; died 2011.

1939 Peter Revson, race car driver; died 1974

1940 Bill Hunter, actor; died 2011.

1943 Mary Frann, actress; died 1998

1951 Lee Atwater, political strategist and advisor; died 1991.
